<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; padding-bottom: 5px; margin-top=
: 30px; margin-bottom: 0;">Exxon</h2><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">It=E2=80=
=99s only a slight overstatement to say that, every year, every publicly tr=
aded oil company asks its shareholders to vote on a proposal like this:</p>=
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">RESOLVED: Shareholders request tha=
t ExxonMobil=E2=80=99s Board of Directors issue an audited report to shareh=
olders on whether and how a significant reduction in fossil fuel demand, en=
visioned in the IEA Net Zero 2050 scenario, would affect its financial posi=
tion and underlying assumptions. The Board should summarize its findings to=
 shareholders by January 31, 2022, and the report should be completed at re=
asonable cost and omitting proprietary information.</p></blockquote><p styl=
e=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Oil companies are at the center of debates over clima=
te change. Many investors care a lot about climate change. Shareholders of =
public companies are, in some loose sense, the owners of those companies; t=
hey elect the directors of the companies and have some authority to tell th=
ose directors what to do.=C2=A0In particular, a shareholder of a U.S. publi=
c company can submit=C2=A0proposals for other shareholders to vote on in th=
e company=E2=80=99s annual proxy statement. Companies have to include the p=
roposals in their proxy statements =E2=80=94=C2=A0that is, put them to a vo=
te of shareholders =E2=80=94=C2=A0unless they can find some reason to omit =
them. The rule (<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/23=
970292.271103/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubGF3LmNvcm5lbGwuZWR1L2Nmci90ZXh0LzE3LzI0MC4xN=
GEtOA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB74e2a697" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=
=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; b=
order-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style:=
 solid; background-color: #ccc;">Rule 14a-8</a>)=C2=A0gives companies lots =
of reasons to omit proposals, and there is a certain amount of technical la=
wyering involved in getting a proposal into a proxy statement. In particula=
r, companies can omit a proposal that =E2=80=9Cdeals with a matter relating=
 to the company=E2=80=99s ordinary business operations,=E2=80=9D which mean=
s that shareholders can=E2=80=99t really submit proposals like =E2=80=9Cyou=
 should stop drilling for oil so much.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=9CYou should write a=
 report about oil drilling=E2=80=9D is usually fine.</p><p style=3D"margin:=
 16px 0;">The proposal I quoted above is Item 6 of <a href=3D"https://link.=
mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/23970292.271103/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi=
9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzM0MDg4LzAwMDExOTMxMjUyMTA4MjE0MC9kOTQxNTlkZGVmY=
zE0YS5odG0jdG9jOTQxNTlfMjA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBcc89f00d" itemprop=3D"S=
toryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration:=
 none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; b=
order-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">Exxon Mobil Corp.=E2=80=
=99s proxy statement</a> this year. It was proposed by Christian Brothers I=
nvestment Services Inc., which owns Exxon =E2=80=9Cshares with a market val=
ue greater than $2,000.=E2=80=9D Here=E2=80=99s one from Exxon=E2=80=99s <a=
 href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/23970292.271103/aHR0=
cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzM0MDg4LzAwMDExOTMxMjUyMDE=
